You can submit feedback or patches on github, or by sending email to
the public mailing list at ~krobelus/kakoune@lists.sr.ht (archives:
https://lists.sr.ht/~krobelus/kakoune).

By contributing you agree to release your code under the project's licensing
model (see COPYING for details).

When contributing your first changes, please include an empty commit for
copyright waiver using the following message (replace 'John Doe' with
your name or nickname):

  John Doe Copyright Waiver

  I dedicate any and all copyright interest in this software to the
  public domain.  I make this dedication for the benefit of the public at
  large and to the detriment of my heirs and successors.  I intend this
  dedication to be an overt act of relinquishment in perpetuity of all
  present and future rights to this software under copyright law.


Changelog workflow:

The changelog for the upcoming release is drafted in the "changelog" branch
in the repository. This branch is frequently rewound; it has only one commit
that is merged to master before each release.
